Instruction 1: LUBRICATE AND INSPECT ALL PNEUMATIC COMPONENTS. REPAIR AS NEEDED.
INSPECT BUTTER APPLICATOR CYLINDERS AND SEALS FOR LEAKS OR DAMAGED PARTS. REPLACE AS NEEDED.
INSPECT ELECTRICAL COMPONENTS FOR DAMAGE. REPAIR OR REPLACE AS NEEDED.
CHECK CONDITION OF ALL MACHINE GUARDS, REPAIR OR REPLACE ANY MISSING GUARDS
CHECK CONDITION OF CUTTER/SEAL BAR ASSEMBLY. REPLACE KNIFE AND ANVIL IF THEY ARE SHOWING EXCESSIVE WEAR.
LUBRICATE AND INSPECT ALL MECHANICAL COMPONENTS INCLUDING BEARINGS, SHAFTS, BELTS, ROLLS, WEAR STRIPS, BUSHINGS, LINKAGES, BRAKE UNITS, CHAINS AND SPROCKETS.
LUBRICATE AND INSPECT ALL PNEUMATIC COMPONENTS. REPAIR OR REPLACE IF NEEDED.
CHECK CONDITION OF ALL MACHINE GUARDS, REPAIR OR REPLACE ANY MISSING GUARDS
CHECK OIL LEVEL AND CONDITION IN GEARBOXES. REPLACE OIL OR REPLACE GEARBOX IF NEEDED.
INSPECT ELECTRICAL COMPONENTS FOR DAMAGE. REPAIR OR REPLACE AS NEEDED.
INSPECT CONDITION AND OPERATION OF SLICER BLADES DRIVE PULLEYS, BEARINGS, SHAFTS, SPINDLES, GUIDES, AND TENSIONER.
INSPECT CONDITION AND OPERATION OF SLICER PRESSURE BELTS, PRESSURE BELT ROLLERS AND DRIVE ASSEMBLY. REPLACE WORN BELTS OR OTHER COMPONENTS IF NEEDED.
INSPECT CONDITION AND OPERATION OF SLICER BLADE MOTOR, DRIVE BELT, PULLEYS AND BRAKE UNIT.
LUBE AND INSPECT BLADE HEIGHT ADJUSTING ASSEMBLY. CHECK HEIGHT ADJUSTMENT FOR PARALLEL. ADJUST LINKAGE IF NEEDED.
REMOVE THE SLICER BLADES, CLEAN AND LUBRICATE STEMS WITH PETROLATUM.  CHECK THE CONDITION OF THE SLEEVES AND O-RINGS.  REPLACE IF NEEDED.
CHECK THAT THE SLICER BLADES ARE ALL AT THE SAME HEIGHT, I.E. LEVEL WITH EACH OTHER.  ADJUST IF NEEDED.
CHECK THE OPERATION AND CONDITION OF THE SCREWDRIVERS AND THE UPPER AND LOWER DRIVE O-RINGS.  REPLACE OR REPAIR IF NEEDED.
INSPECT CONDITION AND OPERATION OF SLICER BLADE DRIVE PULLEYS, BEARINGS, SHAFTS, GUIDES, AND TENSIONER.
INSPECT CONDITION AND OPERATION OF SLICER PRESSURE BELTS, PRESSURE BELT ROLLERS AND DRIVE ASSEMBLY. REPLACE WORN BELTS OR OTHER COMPONENTS IF NEEDED.
INSPECT CONDITION AND OPERATION OF SLICER BLADE, MOTOR, DRIVE BELT, PULLEYS AND BRAKE UNIT.
LUBE AND INSPECT BLADE HEIGHT ADJUSTING ASSEMBLY. CHECK HEIGHT ADJUSTMENT FOR PARALLEL. ADJUST LINKAGE IF NEEDED.
LUBRICATE AND INSPECT CONDITION OF ALL PNEUMATIC COMPONENTS. REPAIR OR REPLACE PARTS AS NEEDED
LUBRICATE AND INSPECT ALL MECHANICAL COMPONENTS, INCLUDING BELTS, CHAINS, SPROCKETS, BUSHINGS, LINKAGES, CAMS, CLUTCHES, BEARINGS, SHAFTS, GUIDES AND WEAR STRIPS. REPAIR AS NEEDED.
CHECK CONDITION AND OPERATION OF ALL ELECTRICAL COMPONENTS. REPAIR OR REPLACE AS NEEDED.
BLOW OUT MOTORS AND FAN AREAS. IF NECESSARY REMOVE FAN COVER.
INSPECT ALL DETENT CLUTCHES FOR PROPER OPERATION. ADJUST OR REPLACE AS NEEDED.
CHECK OIL LEVEL AND CONDITION OF OIL IN ALL GEARBOXES. REPLACE OIL OR REPLACE THE GEARBOX DEPENDING ON THE CONDITION. IF NECESSARY TAKE A SAMPLE TO SEND OUT FOR ANALYSIS.
INSPECT ALL GUARDS INCLUDING SLICER GUARDS. MAKE SURE THEY ARE ATTACHED PROPERLY AND SAFETIES ARE WORKING.
LUBRICATE AND INSPECT ALL MECHANICAL COMPONENTS INCLUDING CHAINS, SPROCKETS, BELTS, PULLEYS, LINKAGES, PUSHERS, GUIDES AND WEAR STRIPS. REPAIR AS NEEDED
CHECK OIL LEVEL AND CONDITION IN GEARBOXES. DEPENDING ON CONDITION REPLACE OIL OR REPLACE THE GEARBOX.
CHECK CONDITION OF ALL MACHINE GUARDS, REPAIR OR REPLACE ANY MISSING GUARDS
INSPECT ELECTRICAL COMPONENTS FOR DAMAGE. REPAIR OR REPLACE AS NEEDED
LUBRICATE AND INSPECT ALL PNEUMATIC COMPONENTS REPLACE AS NEEDED.

CHECK OPERATION AND CONDITION OF PRINTER ASSEMBLY, REPAIR OR REPLACE COMPONENTS AS NEEDED.
CHECK CONDITION OF BRUSH ASSEMBLY. CLEAN DEBRIS OUT OF CHAINS AND SPROCKETS, REPLACE WORN OUT CHAINS AS NEEDED, INSPECT ALL MECHANICAL COMPONENTS AND REPAIR AS NEEDED.
INSPECT ELECTRICAL COMPONENTS FOR DAMAGE. REPAIR OR REPLACE AS NEEDED.
CHECK CALIBRATION ACCURACY OF ALL INGREDIENT METERS. USE THE INGREDIENT METER CHECK FORM TO LOG THE READINGS. MAKE ANY ADJUSTMENTS OR REPAIRS IF NEEDED TO RESTORE ACCURACY.
